<tool id="lm_get_samples" name="Get LMDB Samples" version="0.1.0+galaxy0" python_template_version="3.5" profile="21.05">
    <requirements>
        <requirement type="package" version="2.2.3">pandas</requirement>
        <requirement type="package" version="2.9.9">psycopg2</requirement>
        <requirement type="package" version="2.0.37">sqlalchemy</requirement>
    </requirements>
    <command detect_errors="exit_code"><![CDATA[
        python '$__tool_directory__'/get_samples.py
        --login-name $login
        --input-file $projects
        --output-file $samples
    ]]></command>
    <inputs>
        <param name="login" type="text" optional="false" label="UFZ Login Name" help="Lambda-Miner login name which equals the UFZ login name."/>
        <param name="projects" type="data" format="csv" optional="false" label="Projects" help="Input file containing a single project"/>
    </inputs>
    <outputs>
        <data name="samples" format="csv" label="Samples"/>
    </outputs>
    <tests>
        <test>
            <param name="login" value="dummy_bgo"/>
            <param name="projects" value="test_projects_single.csv"/>
            <output name="samples" file="test_samples_single.csv" ftype="csv" compare="contains"/>
        </test>
        <test>
            <param name="login" value="dummy_bgo"/>
            <param name="projects" value="test_projects_multiple.csv"/>
            <output name="samples" file="test_samples_multiple.csv" ftype="csv" compare="contains"/>
        </test>
    </tests>
    <help><![CDATA[
**What it does**

This tool quries the Lambda-Miner database for samples of the given project.

**Input**

There is a input including the selected project necessary.
The tool connects to the Lambda-Miner database and uses the users login name to
query it.

**Output**

CSV file containing the samples corresponding to the project.]]>
    </help>
    <citations>
        <citation type="doi">10.5194/egusphere-egu24-15782</citation>
    </citations>
</tool>
